AFTER:
for (let i = this.events.length - 1; i >= 0 && result.length < this.maxRecentApps; i--) {
  const app = this.events[i].appName
  if (seen.has(app)) {
    continue
  }
  seen.add(app)
  result.push(app)
}

WHY: Moves the length check into the loop guard (eliminating the nested break) and inverts the Set membership check to a continue guard clause, reducing nesting from 3 to 2 levels.
